In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims November 2011 as National Adoption Month. He emphasizes the importance of ensuring the health and well-being of children and acknowledges that there are still over 100,000 children in America waiting for permanent homes. The President praises the acts of compassion and love that unite children with adoptive families and encourages all qualified caregivers, regardless of race, religion, sexual orientation, or marital status, to have the opportunity to serve as adoptive parents. The article also mentions the efforts of the Obama Administration in supporting adoptive families and children in need, such as signing the Child and Family Services Improvement and Innovation Act, the Healthy, Hunger-Free Kids Act, and the International Adoption Simplification Act. The President reiterates the importance of giving children the love of a family and a permanent home, and encourages Americans to find homes for every child in need and support the families who care for them.